{
  "text": "The attachment process results in two current waves moving in opposite directions, one ascending toward the cloud and the other one descending toward ground [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The latter current wave is expected to be reflected at the ground and catch up with the upward-moving current wave to form a single, upward-moving wave [CITATION_4] , which is traditionally viewed as the return stroke proper.",
